title: Were the French, but not Trump, attending WW1 services at Arlington National Cemetery?
subtitle: French officials participated in Veterans' Day Services at Arlington National Cemetery on the occasion of the centennial of the WW1 Conclusion.
author: Alex Kasprak
vclaim: President Trump did not attend the Veterans ' Day service at Arlington National Cemetery on the occasion of the 100th anniversary of the end of the First World War, but the representatives of the French Government attended.
